                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-04T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 4, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Your 1, January 3, 8 p.m. On January 9, Ralph Cady and assistant, Julio del
                    Pino, will sail from Callao for Arica. Señor del Pino is a Peruvian citizen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
